data: The corresponding traditional form character U+298CA 𩣊 xù (GHZ-74552.10) has the form ⿰馬戌, but is written as ⿰馬戍 in Hanyu Da Zidian p. 4845 and Zhonghua Zihai p. 1651, so the G-source glyph may be a mistake.  Note that some other characters with 戍 phonetic are also read xù (e.g. U+3CDA 㳚, U+4389 䎉, U+25395 𥎕).
